"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-25-Olympic-related-activities-set-for-mini-World-s-Fair-at-park-in-Paris-1vw7VdD41zi-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Scene  Copied  A stage at Club France in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.3897054607857423e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995273059003048, \"rank\": 0.000458871941009901, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/AP  Sip a cool caipirinha cocktail in Brazil.\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 307, \"end\": 313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9997567447913119, \"rank\": 0.00024329972323436255, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sample a spicy samosa in India.\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 340, \"end\": 345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9972541656734617, \"rank\": 0.0023715270573500136, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boogie down with a DJ in France until the early hours.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995273059003048, \"rank\": 0.000458871941009901, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or do all three in a day \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 and perhaps meet some athletes as well.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers want fans who are in Paris, but do not have tickets for the Olympics, to know that they can spend their days \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 and perhaps boozy nights \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 at the Parc des Nations, or Nations Park, which is hosting 15 festive national team clubhouses in what amounts to a mini-World's Fair on the edge of Paris.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.3897054607857423e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 1.3897054607857423e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project gives a temporary new name to the Parc de la Villette in the northeast corner of the French capital.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 828, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Parc de la Villette\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\"}, {\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9994765881830421, \"rank\": 0.0002908092703277881, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will open on Saturday, once Friday's ambitious Opening Ceremony on the River Seine is over, along with its enormous security demands.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.978029888454192, \"rank\": 0.018780503632052446, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine one huge, multicultural fan zone.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea is for visitors to connect with each other, with Olympic athletes and with the Games themselves, organizers said.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The slogan of these Olympics is 'Games Wide Open,' and we wanted to bring that to life,\\\" said Amelie Guignabert of Paris 2024, the Olympic organizing committee.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.0098658998833218e-13, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We really believe in it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All they need, she noted, will be the fans, and officials are advertising on the Paris Metro and elsewhere.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"score\": 0.9999998407888724, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Metro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Certainly, there is room for them.\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest house is, not surprisingly, Club France, which can accommodate 5,000 to 6,000 people inside, and 20,000 in the outside spaces, which include two huge fields.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995273059003048, \"rank\": 0.000458871941009901, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other team clubhouses are Casa Brazil, Canada Team House, Casa Colombia, Czech House, India House, Casa Mexico, Team NL (Netherlands) House, Mongolia House, Serbian House, Slovak House, Slovenian House, and Ekhaya South Africa.\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9997567447913119, \"rank\": 0.00024329972323436255, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1749, \"title\": 